---
<Layout title="The Biggest Bitcoin Price Crashes in History | xCrypto24" description="Explore the largest Bitcoin crashes — from Mt. Gox to COVID to FTX. Learn what caused each crash, how deep they went, and how long recovery took." keywords="bitcoin crashes, bitcoin price crash, crypto crash history, bitcoin bear market, Mt Gox crash, FTX collapse, bitcoin drawdowns">
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"The Biggest Bitcoin Price Crashes in History","description":"Explore the largest Bitcoin crashes — from Mt. Gox to COVID to FTX. Learn what caused each crash, how deep they went, and how long recovery took.","datePublished":"2026-06-16","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"xCrypto24","url":"https://xcrypto24.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"xCrypto24"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://xcrypto24.com/blog/biggest-bitcoin-crashes"}})} />
  <div style="max-width:700px;margin:2rem auto;padding:0 1rem;">
    <nav style="font-size:0.8rem;color:#71717a;margin-bottom:1.5rem;">
      <a href="/blog" style="color:#c084fc;text-decoration:none;">← Blog</a> › <span style="color:#a1a1aa;">History</span>
    </nav>
    <article>
      <h1 style="font-size:2rem;font-weight:700;color:#fafafa;margin-bottom:0.5rem;">The Biggest Bitcoin Price Crashes in History</h1>
      <div style="display:flex;gap:0.8rem;font-size:0.8rem;color:#71717a;margin-bottom:2rem;">
        <time datetime="2026-06-16">June 16, 2026</time><span>·</span><span>10 min read</span>
      </div>
      <p style="font-size:1.05rem;line-height:1.7;color:#d4d4d8;margin-bottom:2rem;">Bitcoin has been declared dead over 470 times. Each time it crashed violently — 50%, 70%, even 93% — and each time it recovered to new all-time highs. Understanding these crashes isn't just history; it's a survival guide. The patterns repeat, the causes rhyme, and the recoveries follow predictable timelines.</p>

      <div style="padding:1rem;border-radius:10px;border:1px solid rgba(139,92,246,0.3);background:rgba(139,92,246,0.05);margin:1.5rem 0;display:flex;justify-content:space-around;text-align:center;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:1rem;">
        <div><p style="font-size:1.3rem;font-weight:700;color:#c084fc;">470+</p><p style="font-size:0.75rem;color:#71717a;">"Bitcoin Is Dead" Articles</p></div>
        <div><p style="font-size:1.3rem;font-weight:700;color:#c084fc;">-93%</p><p style="font-size:0.75rem;color:#71717a;">Deepest Single Crash</p></div>
        <div><p style="font-size:1.3rem;font-weight:700;color:#c084fc;">100%</p><p style="font-size:0.75rem;color:#71717a;">Recovery Rate (so far)</p></div>
      </div>

      <h2 style="font-size:1.3rem;font-weight:600;color:#c084fc;margin:2rem 0 1rem;padding-left:0.8rem;border-left:3px solid #8b5cf6;">1. The First Crash: June 2011 (-93%)</h2>
      <p style="font-size:0.95rem;line-height:1.7;color:#d4d4d8;margin-bottom:1rem;">Bitcoin's first major crash took price from $31 to $2 — a 93% wipeout. The trigger was a Mt. Gox hack where an attacker dumped thousands of BTC, crashing the orderbook. Mt. Gox handled virtually all trading volume at the time.</p>

      <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:0.8rem;margin:1.5rem 0;">
        <div style="padding:1rem;border-radius:8px;border:1px solid rgba(239,68,68,0.3);background:rgba(239,68,68,0.05);">
          <p style="color:#f87171;font-weight:600;font-size:0.85rem;margin-bottom:0.3rem;">📉 The Crash</p>
          <p style="color:#a1a1aa;font-size:0.8rem;">$31 → $2 in weeks. Thin liquidity exposed. Total market cap below $50M.</p>
        </div>
        <div style="padding:1rem;border-radius:8px;border:1px solid rgba(34,197,94,0.3);background:rgba(34,197,94,0.05);">
          <p style="color:#4ade80;font-weight:600;font-size:0.85rem;margin-bottom:0.3rem;">📈 Recovery</p>
          <p style="color:#a1a1aa;font-size:0.8rem;">2 years to reclaim $31. By late 2013, hit $1,100 — a 35x gain from crash low.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 style="font-size:1.3rem;font-weight:600;color:#c084fc;margin:2rem 0 1rem;padding-left:0.8rem;border-left:3px solid #8b5cf6;">2. Mt. Gox Collapse: 2014 (-87%)</h2>
      <p style="font-size:0.95rem;line-height:1.7;color:#d4d4d8;margin-bottom:1rem;">After reaching $1,100 in November 2013, Bitcoin entered a 13-month decline. Mt. Gox revealed 850,000 BTC ($450M) had been stolen over years. The exchange filed bankruptcy. Trust collapsed.</p>

      <div style="padding:1rem;border-radius:10px;border:1px solid rgba(139,92,246,0.3);background:rgba(139,92,246,0.05);margin:1.5rem 0;display:flex;justify-content:space-around;text-align:center;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:1rem;">
        <div><p style="font-size:1.3rem;font-weight:700;color:#c084fc;">$1,100</p><p style="font-size:0.75rem;color:#71717a;">Peak (Nov 2013)</p></div>
        <div><p style="font-size:1.3rem;font-weight:700;color:#c084fc;">$150</p><p style="font-size:0.75rem;color:#71717a;">Bottom (Jan 2015)</p></div>
        <div><p style="font-size:1.3rem;font-weight:700;color:#c084fc;">3 years</p><p style="font-size:0.75rem;color:#71717a;">To Recover $1,100</p></div>
      </div>

      <div style="padding:1rem 1.2rem;border-radius:10px;border:1px solid rgba(34,197,94,0.3);background:rgba(34,197,94,0.05);margin:1.5rem 0;">
        <p style="color:#4ade80;font-weight:600;font-size:0.8rem;margin-bottom:0.3rem;">💡 LESSON LEARNED</p>
        <p style="color:#d4d4d8;font-size:0.9rem;">Never store significant amounts on exchanges. "Not your keys, not your coins" became the mantra — a lesson painfully relearned with FTX eight years later.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 style="font-size:1.3rem;font-weight:600;color:#c084fc;margin:2rem 0 1rem;padding-left:0.8rem;border-left:3px solid #8b5cf6;">3. The ICO Bust: 2018 (-84%)</h2>
      <p style="font-size:0.95rem;line-height:1.7;color:#d4d4d8;margin-bottom:1rem;">The 2017 bull was fueled by ICO speculation — thousands of projects raised billions with nothing but a whitepaper. When retail investors who'd never seen a bear market flooded in at $20,000, the crash was merciless: 84% over 12 months to $3,122.</p>

      <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:0.8rem;margin:1.5rem 0;">
        <div style="padding:1rem;border-radius:8px;border:1px solid rgba(6,182,212,0.3);background:rgba(6,182,212,0.05);">
          <p style="color:#06b6d4;font-weight:600;font-size:0.85rem;margin-bottom:0.3rem;">📊 The Damage</p>
          <p style="color:#a1a1aa;font-size:0.8rem;">Total market: $800B → $100B. 90% of ICO tokens went to zero. Companies laid off 80% of staff.</p>
        </div>
        <div style="padding:1rem;border-radius:8px;border:1px solid rgba(6,182,212,0.3);background:rgba(6,182,212,0.05);">
          <p style="color:#06b6d4;font-weight:600;font-size:0.85rem;margin-bottom:0.3rem;">⏱️ Recovery</p>
          <p style="color:#a1a1aa;font-size:0.8rem;">$20K reclaimed December 2020 — 3 years later. Then surged to $69K in 11 months.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 style="font-size:1.3rem;font-weight:600;color:#c084fc;margin:2rem 0 1rem;padding-left:0.8rem;border-left:3px solid #8b5cf6;">4. COVID Black Thursday: March 2020 (-50% in 24hrs)</h2>
      <p style="font-size:0.95rem;line-height:1.7;color:#d4d4d8;margin-bottom:1rem;">On March 12, 2020, Bitcoin crashed from $8,000 to $3,800 in a single day. COVID-19 panic triggered a global liquidity crisis. Cascading liquidations on leveraged platforms amplified selling. It was the fastest crash in Bitcoin history.</p>

      <div style="padding:1rem;border-radius:10px;border:1px solid rgba(139,92,246,0.3);background:rgba(139,92,246,0.05);margin:1.5rem 0;display:flex;justify-content:space-around;text-align:center;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:1rem;">
        <div><p style="font-size:1.3rem;font-weight:700;color:#c084fc;">-50%</p><p style="font-size:0.75rem;color:#71717a;">In 24 Hours</p></div>
        <div><p style="font-size:1.3rem;font-weight:700;color:#c084fc;">$1B+</p><p style="font-size:0.75rem;color:#71717a;">Liquidations</p></div>
        <div><p style="font-size:1.3rem;font-weight:700;color:#c084fc;">55 days</p><p style="font-size:0.75rem;color:#71717a;">Full Recovery</p></div>
      </div>

      <p style="font-size:0.95rem;line-height:1.7;color:#d4d4d8;margin-bottom:1rem;">What made COVID unique: recovery was extraordinarily fast. Within 55 days, Bitcoin was back at pre-crash levels. Within a year, $60,000. It proved BTC sells off with risk assets in liquidity crises but recovers faster.</p>

      <h2 style="font-size:1.3rem;font-weight:600;color:#c084fc;margin:2rem 0 1rem;padding-left:0.8rem;border-left:3px solid #8b5cf6;">5. FTX Contagion: 2022 (-77%)</h2>
      <p style="font-size:0.95rem;line-height:1.7;color:#d4d4d8;margin-bottom:1rem;">2022 was death by a thousand cuts. The bear market chain of failures:</p>

      <div style="padding:1rem 1.2rem;border-radius:10px;border:1px solid rgba(239,68,68,0.3);background:rgba(239,68,68,0.05);margin:1.5rem 0;">
        <p style="color:#f87171;font-weight:600;font-size:0.8rem;margin-bottom:0.3rem;">⚠️ 2022 DOMINO EFFECT</p>
        <p style="color:#d4d4d8;font-size:0.9rem;margin-bottom:0.5rem;"><strong style="color:#fafafa;">May:</strong> Luna/Terra collapse. $40B algorithmic stablecoin fails in 72 hours.</p>
        <p style="color:#d4d4d8;font-size:0.9rem;margin-bottom:0.5rem;"><strong style="color:#fafafa;">June:</strong> Three Arrows Capital defaults on $3.5B. Cascading liquidations.</p>
        <p style="color:#d4d4d8;font-size:0.9rem;margin-bottom:0.5rem;"><strong style="color:#fafafa;">July:</strong> Celsius, Voyager freeze withdrawals. Billions locked.</p>
        <p style="color:#d4d4d8;font-size:0.9rem;"><strong style="color:#fafafa;">Nov:</strong> FTX fraud exposed. $8B customer funds missing. SBF arrested.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 style="font-size:1.3rem;font-weight:600;color:#c084fc;margin:2rem 0 1rem;padding-left:0.8rem;border-left:3px solid #8b5cf6;">Patterns Across All Crashes</h2>

      <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:0.8rem;margin:1.5rem 0;">
        <div style="padding:1rem;border-radius:8px;border:1px solid rgba(139,92,246,0.3);background:rgba(139,92,246,0.05);">
          <p style="color:#c084fc;font-weight:600;font-size:0.85rem;margin-bottom:0.3rem;">Depth</p>
          <p style="color:#a1a1aa;font-size:0.8rem;">77-93% from peak. Average bear bottom is ~80% below the high.</p>
        </div>
        <div style="padding:1rem;border-radius:8px;border:1px solid rgba(139,92,246,0.3);background:rgba(139,92,246,0.05);">
          <p style="color:#c084fc;font-weight:600;font-size:0.85rem;margin-bottom:0.3rem;">Duration</p>
          <p style="color:#a1a1aa;font-size:0.8rem;">Bear markets 12-18 months. Recovery to new ATH takes 2-3 years from bottom.</p>
        </div>
        <div style="padding:1rem;border-radius:8px;border:1px solid rgba(139,92,246,0.3);background:rgba(139,92,246,0.05);">
          <p style="color:#c084fc;font-weight:600;font-size:0.85rem;margin-bottom:0.3rem;">Trigger</p>
          <p style="color:#a1a1aa;font-size:0.8rem;">Leverage + fraud + external shock. Speculation builds fragility that one event exposes.</p>
        </div>
        <div style="padding:1rem;border-radius:8px;border:1px solid rgba(139,92,246,0.3);background:rgba(139,92,246,0.05);">
          <p style="color:#c084fc;font-weight:600;font-size:0.85rem;margin-bottom:0.3rem;">Recovery</p>
          <p style="color:#a1a1aa;font-size:0.8rem;">Every crash followed by new ATH. Each bottom higher than the previous cycle's bottom.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div style="padding:1rem 1.2rem;border-radius:10px;border:1px solid rgba(34,197,94,0.3);background:rgba(34,197,94,0.05);margin:1.5rem 0;">
        <p style="color:#4ade80;font-weight:600;font-size:0.8rem;margin-bottom:0.3rem;">💡 SURVIVAL LESSON</p>
        <p style="color:#d4d4d8;font-size:0.9rem;">The investors who made the most money share one trait: they held through crashes. Not because they weren't scared — because they sized positions so they could afford to hold. The key isn't predicting crashes; it's surviving them.</p>
      </div>

